                                localtype="box">1</container>
                     <container id="aspace_2e81c97a67b833e710bb9acbd9bd98ee"
                                localtype="folder"
                                parent="aspace_44090634391b1b5bf1bfaa8ef0e2a597">8</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_4c96518085fea3b4af6c0c858b91ff4a">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Two press photographs from the Spanish Civil War. Paris, London: Photos NYT, Keystone View Company, 1936, with dittoed agency notes pasted to reverse. One photograph (9.5 inches by 7.5 inches) depicts "Xmas dinner on the Spanish War Front, picture by air from our own correspondent," or government soldiers on the Valdemero-Pinto section of the Madrid front eating Christmas dinner, and is dated 1936 December 28. A second photograph (7 inches x 5 inches) depicts a man with a gun standing by a bombed-out building, with caption on the back reading "Les dégâts causés à une maison de Geusa (Aragon) par une grenade bombe de l'artillerie nationale," and is dated 1936 October 20.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
